comment: Alternate proof of ~ 2irrexpq : There exist irrational numbers ` a ` and ` b ` such that ` ( a ^ b ) ` is rational. Statement in the Metamath book, section 1.1.5, footnote 27 on page 17, and the "constructive proof" for theorem 1.2 of [Bauer], p. 483. In contrast to ~ 2irrexpq , this is a constructive proof because it is based on two explicitly named irrational numbers ` ( sqrt `` 2 ) ` and ` ( 2 logb 9 ) ` , see ~ sqrt2irr0 , ~ 2logb9irr and ~ sqrt2cxp2logb9e3 . Therefore, this proof is also acceptable/usable in intuitionistic logic. (Contributed by AV, 23-Dec-2022.) (New usage is discouraged.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)
